# ==============================================================================
# 1. FETCH NOTIFICATIONS (WITH FILTERS & PAGINATION)
# ==============================================================================
# Notes:
# - recipient: Automatically determined on backend from user session (Bearer token).
#
# Pagination:
# - page (integer): Current page number (default: 1)
# - limit (integer): Number of notifications per page (default: 10)
#
# Filters:
# - isRead (boolean, optional): Filter by read state (true/false)
# - type (string, optional): Filter by notification type.
#   Valid types: ["EVENT", "COURSE", "CHAT", "FOLLOW", "USER", "SYSTEM", "REVIEW", "PAYOUT"]
# ==============================================================================

### 1a. Fetch Filtered Notifications (e.g., Unread EVENT notifications)
GET {{baseUrl}}/notification/my-notifications?page=1&limit=10&type=EVENT
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 1b. Fetch All Notifications (Default Pagination, No Filters)
GET {{baseUrl}}/notification/my-notifications?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 1c. Fetch Bookings Category Notifications
GET {{baseUrl}}/notification/my-notifications?page=1&limit=10&category=
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 1d. Fetch Payments Category Notifications
GET {{baseUrl}}/notification/my-notifications?page=1&limit=10&category=payments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 1e. Fetch Event Updates Category Notifications
GET {{baseUrl}}/notification/my-notifications?page=1&limit=10&category=eventupdates
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


# ==============================================================================
# 2. MARK NOTIFICATIONS AS READ
# ==============================================================================
# Notes:
# - /mark-read: Expects a specific notificationId in the JSON body.
# - /mark-all-read: Marks all unread notifications of the logged-in user as read.
# ==============================================================================

### 2a. Mark Single Notification as Read
POST {{baseUrl}}/notification/mark-read
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notificationId": "{{notificationId}}"
}

### 2b. Mark All Notifications as Read
POST {{baseUrl}}/notification/mark-all-read
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}


# ==============================================================================
# 3. DELETE NOTIFICATIONS (SOFT DELETE)
# ==============================================================================
# Notes:
# - /delete: Soft deletes a single notification (sets isDeleted = true).
# - /delete-multiple: Soft deletes multiple notifications matching the provided array.
# ==============================================================================

### 3a. Delete Single Notification
POST {{baseUrl}}/notification/delete
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notificationId": "{{notificationId}}"
}

### 3b. Delete Multiple Notifications
POST {{baseUrl}}/notification/delete-multiple
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notificationIds": [
    "{{notificationId}}"
  ]
}
